               <head>Court reports on Sa‘adat ‘Ali Khan, Nawab of Awadh</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Akhbār</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85033556 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064915 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2009117885 http://lccn.loc.gov/n88138928 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008116463" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4342-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Reports or akhbār, here entitled <title>Zubdat al-akhbārāt</title>, on events and transactions of <persName key="person_f7455" role="subject">Navvāb Vazīr al-Mamālik Saʿādat ʿAlī Khān Bahādur</persName>’s gubernatorial court and government of Awadh State 
                        </p>
                        <p>Additional reports include: 1) <title>Akhbār-i dyūdhī</title> for <persName key="person_f7310" role="rcp">Mīrzā Jān/Khān entitled Khānazād Khān</persName>; 2) <title>Akhbār-i dyūdhī</title> for the <persName key="person_f7088" role="rcp">Baygum Ṣāḥibah</persName> at <placeName>Fayz̤'ābād (Faizabad)</placeName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Accounts only partially cover the period from 4 Ṣafar 1226/1 March 1811 to 7 Jumādá al-S̲ānī 1226/30 June 1811, comprising records for the months of March, May-June </p>
                        <p>Accounts additionally dated on reverse (recto face) with Gregorian dates </p>
                        <p>Accounts on single leaves and scrolls mounted in volume in English order, with each news or khabar leaf beginning on the verso side and mounted in reverse date order, the first folio being the latest khabar and the last (f. 106) being the earliest </p>
                        <p>Bundles of akhbār constituting sets of dispatches mounted as clusters along upper or lower edges </p>
                        <p>Pencil annotations throughout 
</p>
                        <p>Neat, scribal Indian taʿlīq 
</p>
                        <p>Date of compilation not recorded </p>
                     </note>
